<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc3782967-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s3510"><num value="3510">§ 3510.</num><heading> Eligibility and entitlement generally</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Each eligible person shall, subject to the provisions of this chapter, be entitled to receive educational assistance.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc3782968-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(<ref href="/us/pl/85/857">Pub. L. 85–857</ref>, <date date="1958-09-02">Sept. 2, 1958</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/72/1194">72 Stat. 1194</ref>, § 1710; renumbered § 3510, <ref href="/us/pl/102/83/s5/a">Pub. L. 102–83, § 5(a)</ref>, <date date="1991-08-06">Aug. 6, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/406">105 Stat. 406</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
